# Cochlear Manifold — the Rust workspace (VST3 plugin, DSP kernel, wasm crate).
# 3.8GB of Rust sources and build output that the web image never touches. The
# ONLY manifold files the app imports are index.js and factory-presets.js (via
# src/lib/manifold.adapter.js), and they are self-contained — index.js imports
# nothing from these subtrees, only ../pixelbrain/shared.js. Keep those two.
codex/core/manifold/manifold-core/
codex/core/manifold/manifold-plugin/
codex/core/manifold/manifold-wasm/
codex/core/manifold/rust-kernel/
codex/core/manifold/target/
codex/core/manifold/UI/
codex/core/manifold/Cargo.toml
codex/core/manifold/Cargo.lock
codex/core/manifold/MANIFOLD_WHITEPAPER.md

# Nested Rust build dirs. The bare `target/` rule above is context-root-only
# (Docker does not match it recursively), which is why the manifold target dirs
# were still being shipped. Deliberately NOT `**/rust-kernel` — that would also
# match src/lib/math/quantization/rust-kernel/pkg, which the TurboQuant wasm
# bridge dynamically imports.
**/target/

# Large local SQLite dbs / artifacts not needed at image-build time
